dsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Found druid spell</span><hr size=1> This spell needs to be made stackable with regrowth. In its current form it seems kinda useless when you have a regrowth BP. /feedback :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utrienatwobooks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Triena Twobooks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/10/01 4:56:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Think of it this way</span><hr size=1> <br>Q.  Why do we use regen at all?<br>A.  As a tank regenerates, it means the tank needs healed less often.<br><br>Q. Ok so what the consequenses of a better regen?<br>A. A better regen means tank needs healed less often<br><br>Q. Ok i under stand that, so whats good about Natures recovery?<br>A. Its twice as good as regrowth, so that means the period between heals just got twice as long.<br><br>Q. Why is this good?<br>A. Less agro is the major reason, more med time is the minor reason.<br><br>Q. So why are people still complaning about this spell?<br>A. Cuz they suxor son, just get used to it.<br><br>Twobooks<br>55 Druid of Xev<br><br>~~I dont have to port to be a whore~~<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxenthos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xenthos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/10/01 9:31:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Think of it this way</span><hr size=1> Not quite, Triena.  I've played with the spell a bit, and it doesn't seem so great.  &quot;Twice as long between heals&quot;?  Not quite.  It needs to be refreshed every 3 minutes, with a very long recast delay.  Breastplate lasts much longer, and also heals more over the life of the spell.<br><br>&quot;A. Its twice as good as regrowth, so that means the period between heals just got twice as long.&quot;<br>Also not exact.  CH cancels this bridge- it doesn't care whether the target is at 4 bubbles of health, or has 5 hps remaining.  A cleric will cast CH whenever the tank hits a certain amount of health, whether he's regenned or not.<br><br>&quot;Q. Why is this good?<br>A. Less agro is the major reason, more med time is the minor reason.&quot;<br>There is *LESS* med time with this spell because it needs to be refreshed every three minutes, with 250 mana used each time.<br><br>Good spell for saying, &quot;Looky here, I can kill your regen!&quot; and not much else. <p>-Xen</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utrienatwobooks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Triena Twobooks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/10/01 11:05:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Think of it this way</span><hr size=1> Ah but consider this...<br><br>Your in a camp and the tank is pulling as soon as the last mob dies...<br><br>Your sat there and you watch the tanks heath fall steadily over time...<br><br>If say the cleric CH at 1 bubble...with regrowth on, the time it takes for the tanks heath to fall is buffeded by the +15 tic regen a second.  So it takes longer for the tank to get down to 1 bub, thus the cleric does not have to cast CH as often.<br><br>With the new spell this is now up to +30, so logic says it will take longer for the tank to get down to the 1 bub.<br><br>Is the time from full to 1 bubble doubled? No, but the difference that regrowth made is doubled.<br><br>Do you save mana?  Well if your job is not to heal, then no, but then you save the cleric mana, that is a fact.<br><br>There are times when your mana output is not greater than your mana generation, more often than not this is because you cannot nuke too much as you generate more agro.<br><br>This spell gives us an opertunity to spend mana...its not a waist.<br><br>I too am disapointed that it does not stack with regrowth, personaly i think this should be classified as a heal spell rather than a regen spell, this would make it more useful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/10/01 6:51:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Think of it this way</span><hr size=1> This spell is usefull.  I dont know why people say that if you have velious tunic you would not use this spell.  I would use this spell in many situations and I have the velious tunic.<br><br>Plain and simple, this spell heals 900hp for 250 mana.  Someone said that it is not much different ratio then our current heals.  Umm, it is.  natures touch is something like 450 mana for 948 or around there hp.  That is about 1 mana for 2 hp.  900 for 250mana is almost 1 mana for [b]4[/b]hp.<br><br>Regular situation I would use it in...<br><br>Group:  Regrowth group with tunic, new regen on Main Tank.  The main tank is regen'ing at twice the pace everyone else is, but he is taking the brunt of the hits so its good.  This allows him to heal all the time at 30hp per tick.  This does have an affect on the cleric's mana by far as does our regular regrowth, this is just 2xregrowth.<br><br>Raid:  New regen on Main tank of the raid will help a lot in a cleric's mana.  250 mana at 60 is not much at all...with potg and C2 on (and that is only two of potential 5 mana regen spells/songs) you can regen 250 mana in a couple ticks easily.<br><br>Boss mob:  For a boss mob put the new regen on any possible main tanks so that if one dies the other will have and this will help in keeping their health up over the duration of a potential 2 to 10 minute fight.  <br><br>Dragon/AoE mob:  Every druid cast this on a key pc before they go into the fight as it will help drastically reduce the amount of healing a cleric has to do from the AOE's.  Main tanks are the ones to focus on keeping alive here as well as clerics so those are good targets for this spell, as well as monks, rogues, and possibly wizzards so they can stay in the fight longer and do more damage.<br><br>This is [b]double[/b] our rate of regen as regrowth.  I think the useability of this spell is great and puts us into a good position to help on raids.  Grant it its not a *needed* raid spell, but it will sure help in many situations as I believe if people watch closely they will see how much a higher regen will help them.<br><br>-----------<br>Balise <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47458>My Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxenthos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xenthos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/10/01 7:13:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Think of it this way</span><hr size=1> It's spread out over such a long period of time as to be worthless though.  Look at Celestial Elixir or Torpor for a good wear-off time on &quot;Regen Heals.&quot;  Sure, it will buffer a tank's hps for a few seconds, but if you're pulling experience, mobs will be doubling for 140's, at the least.  The one that drops this spell now hits for 580 a swing (one of them, at least).  Please tell me how 30 hp regen every 6 seconds when a mob is doing over 3,000 damage in that amount of time helps.. answer, it doesn't!  A CH will heal all 3,000 instantly.<br><br>Regen is nice.  It's especially nice in a manaless form like on our tunic.  Regen that needs constant attention and refresh for minimal gain health-wise and much loss mana-wise is pointless.  If this spell stacked with Regrowth, I would use it-- the effect, on its own without any stacking issues, would be decent for normal groups. <p>-Xen</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/11/01 12:29:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Think of it this way</span><hr size=1> You guys are thinking of using this spell as a heal where it is not.  This is a regen spell, that is why it will not stack with regrowth, but will stack with healing spells.  It provides the benefits that a regen spell would, except more because it is a higher level spell.<br><br>Regen spells are usefull in slowing the speed at which the tank goes down in HP.  You can keep this on the tank and only refresh it when the mobs are dead, that equals no extra agro on you, but an extra 900 hps being healed on the tank over three minutes.<br><br>Personally I gain max agro for the first 50% of a mob's life just by hitting it with epic and bracer dot's, so this extra spell to help the group that will cause no extra agro is a good thing.<br><br>Every little bit counts and if you observe closely enough regen spells do make a difference.<br><br>Its only 250 mana for 900 hp.<br><br>------------<br>Balise <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47458>My Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxenthos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xenthos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/11/01 8:50:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Think of it this way</span><hr size=1> &quot;Its only 250 mana for 900 hp.&quot;<br><br>Then:<br><br>&quot;It's only 0 mana for 13,500 hp.&quot; &lt;- Regrowth of the Groves on a full group. <p>-Xen</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/11/01 11:28:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Think of it this way</span><hr size=1> LOL.  Exactly, Xen.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquelm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wolf Elemental</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/11/01 2:46:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 250 mana for 450 hitpoints?  no thanks</span><hr size=1> If you can sneak in chloroblast once every 2 and a half minutes, regrowth + chloroblast is better than keeping nature's recovery on the main tank - in terms of hitpoints healed, time spent casting, mana output, and spell slot usage.<br><br>Regens are good.  In fact, regrowth is better than this one.  That's all I'm saying.<br><br>If nature's recovery stacked with regrowth, it'd be a good spell.  If nature's recovery worked in 15 ticks, it'd be a good spell.  There are a few uses for this spell, namely 3 minute periods when you're hard up against your aggro *and* casting time limits constantly.  (Raids, and some pulls.)<br><br>Remember: with group regrowth, this spell is healing 450 hitpoints for 250 mana.<br><br>-Quelm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/11/01 4:39:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 250 mana for 450 hitpoints?  no thanks</span><hr size=1> "If you can sneak in chloroblast once every 2 and a half minutes, regrowth + chloroblast is better than keeping nature's recovery on the main tank - in terms of hitpoints healed, time spent casting, mana output, and spell slot usage."<br><br><br>True, so not all the situations I mentioned would be right.  Thanks for the insight, I never did think to run those numbers.<br><br><br>"There are a few uses for this spell, namely 3 minute periods when you're hard up against your aggro *and* casting time limits constantly. (Raids, and some pulls.)"<br><br><br>True again.  Though for me these "few" isntances are 70% of my druidic carreer at 60 (level of this spell).  I raid a lot and many situations I can see slapping this on the puller would be a great benefit.  This is how I see this spell being very usefull, I can see if you dont raid then you would see little use for this spell with velious quest tunic.<br><br>For myself and I am guessing many that I know, this spell will be usefull during 70% of their activities in EQ as it will be for me.  It might just be my playstyle, but I am normally at the top of the agro list right at the begining of the fight from initial debuffs, dots, or snares.  I cool down on the agro for the rest of the fight to save it for Evac, extra heals, adds, and such, but this would allow me to cast a benefitial spell that would last the whole fight and more without overagro'ing at the begining.<br><br>-----------<br>Balise<br><br> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47458>My Profile</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balise</A> at: 12/11/01 9:55:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upanamah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Panamah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/26/01 8:39:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2615.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://nmcs.com/kingscourt/images/panamah.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 250 mana for 450 hitpoints?  no thanks</span><hr size=1> It isn't really a regen spell, and it isn't really a heal-over-time spell.  That's the problem with it.  If it was either, I'd suspect druids would be happy.  They should either make it a REAL regen spell and make it last as long as regrowth, or a real HoT spell and have it cure more hit points faster.<br>It does seem really weak.<br><br>Regen on tanks is semi-useless in my opinion.  15 or 30 hit points a tick is nothing when things are hitting you for 100-200 several times a round.  That isn't enough to really postphone much of any healing. The only thing I use regen for these days is to heal the non-tanks.  It takes the pressure off the cleric to have to heal the little boo-boos on people in the group.<br><br>This also assumes the group is good and is constantly pulling and not having any downtime.<br> <p><a href="http://nmcs.com/kingscourt/images/mytrio.jpg">The Three Sopranos</a><br><font size=1><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8428">Panamah,<em> 57th level peculator</em></a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8188"><font size=1>Electrae, <em>High Priestess of Tunare</em></a><br>Wysteria Plushfoot, <em>56 levels of druiding and all I have is this lousy tee-shirt</em></em></font><br><a href="http://nmcs.com/kingscourt"><b>King's Court</b></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulotusflystewnicely.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lotusfly Stewnicely</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/28/01 3:58:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddRep